The paper deals with belief change in logic programming, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). It also involves model theory and semantics of logic programs, which are topics in mathematical logic (cs.LO) and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the use of answer set solvers, which are tools for constraint programming (cs.CC). Finally, the paper deals with merging and revision of logic programs, which are topics in databases (cs.DB).
